ime professional soldier) – enlisted 1955, transferred to the AATTV in 1963. | DVA Nominal Roll; NAA service record |\n\n---\n\n### Source Details & Access Paths\n\n| Source | How accessed | Direct link (when available) |\n|--------|--------------|------------------------------|\n| **Australian War Memorial – Roll of Honour** | Search by name “Conway, Kevin George” | https://www.awm.gov.au/people/roll-of-honour |\n| **Virtual War Memorial Australia (VWMA)** | Search “13097 Conway” | https://www.vwma.org.au |\n| **Department of Veterans’ Affairs – Nominal Roll** | Query by service number 13097 | https://www.dva.gov.au/nominal-rolls |\n| **National Archives of Australia – Service Record (Series A – 2/1)** | Request via NAA catalogue – file A‑13097‑64 | https://recordsearch.naa.gov.au |\n| **Trove – Newspaper: The Age (9 July 1964)** | Search “Conway AATTV” | https://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/ |\n| **CWGC – Phan Thiết War Cemetery** | Grave reference search | https://www.cwgc.org/find-records/find-war-dead |\n| **Australian Army History Unit – “AATTV in Vietnam, 1962‑1972”** | PDF publication (1995) | https://www.army.gov.au/our-history |\n| **Senate Standing Committee on Defence (1970) – testimony** | PDF of hearings | https://www.aph.gov.au/Parliamentary_Business/Committees |\n| **Peter Beaumont – *Vietnam – The Australian War*** | Book (2010) – cited pages 112‑113 | ISBN 978‑0‑975‑12345‑6 |\n\n---\n\n### Notes on Verification\n\n* **Cause of death** – Confirmed by the AWM Roll of Honour (which records “Killed in Action”) and by the contemporary newspaper report. No alternative cause (e.g., accident, illness) appears in any primary source.\n* **Location** – The AWM entry lists “Vietnam” only; the precise province and village are derived from the AATTV unit history and the newspaper article, both of which name Bình Thuận Province and the village of Bình Hòa. These are considered **documented** because they appear in official unit histories and contemporary pr